    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" resp="#JP">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><orig>αυοτ</orig><gap reason="lost" unit="character" quantity="2"/>
                    <lb n="2"/> χρηστὲ κ<unclear>αὶ</unclear>
                    <lb n="3"/>ἄμεμπτε
                    <lb n="4"/>χαῖρε ζήσης
                    <lb n="5"/>ἔτη αβ’
                    <lb n="6"/>μῆνες αι’
               </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus" resp="#JP">
                <listApp>
                    <app><note>Text based upon autopsy</note></app>
                    <app loc="Line 1"><note>2-3 letters follow but are impossible to decipher</note></app>
                    <app loc="Line 2"><note>The traces at the end of the line are compatible with καὶ</note></app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="'#JP">
                <p>Worth and blamless [---], farewell! You lived [-?] years and 11(?) months</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" resp="#JP">
                <p>The stone appears to be unpublished. The name of the deceased is indecipherable. The age in years appears clearly on the stone as αβ, but this is not a standard numeral and it is not obvious how to translate it; the age in months appears to be written in reverse (a phenomenon well attested in Hellenistic Sicily), in which case it is 11.</p>
            </div>
